Class SetHierarchyNode<T extends Serializable>

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
HierarchyNode<T,SetHierarchyNode<T>>, Serializable, Iterable<SetHierarchyNode<T>>
public class SetHierarchyNode<T extends Serializable>
extends AbstractHierarchyNode<T,SetHierarchyNode<T>>
implements Serializable

A node in a simple hierarchy, where a value of the given generic type is attached at each node. The children are stored in a Set and are thus unordered.

registerChild

public void registerChild(SetHierarchyNode<T> child)
Description copied from interface: HierarchyNode
Adds a child node. Does not update the child's parent link! The relationship is primarily owned by the child, so child.setParent() should call this method, not the other way around.

Description copied from interface: HierarchyNode
